Generate a longitudinal record for this specific synthetic patient: {{individual_description}}

* your output should be a JSON object: {"finished": true/false, "records": {time: [[code_system, code_desc, numeric_value, unit], ...], ...}}
* generate events sequentially by time, building the record incrementally
* set "finished": true only if you have completed the full record spanning from {{start_date}} to {{end_date}}; otherwise set "finished": false
* time: string key (ISO timestamp to appropriate precision; use date precision (YYYY-MM-DD) for claims and EHR outpatient, datetime for EHR inpatient; use patient's birthday for static/person-level measurements)
* code_system: the vocabulary system for this code (must be one of: {% if record_type == 'claims' %}icd9_proc, icd10_proc, cpt, icd9, ndc, icd10{% elif record_type in ['ehr-inpatient', 'ehr-outpatient'] %}snomed, rxnorm, icd9_proc, lnc, icd10_proc, cpt, icd9, icd10{% endif %})
* code_desc: brief textual description of the measurement/event (not the code itself)
* numeric_value: numeric result if applicable, else null
* unit: unit for the numeric_value if applicable, else null

* include static measurements for gender, race, and ethnicity
* begin the trajectory on their birthday with birth-related descriptions
* the record should span from {{start_date}} to {{end_date}} (ISO timestamps)
* aim for an average of {{avg_codes_per_time}} codes per timestamp, but allow substantial variation
* this is {% if record_type == 'claims' %}a claims{% elif record_type == 'ehr-inpatient' %}an EHR inpatient{% elif record_type == 'ehr-outpatient' %}an EHR outpatient{% endif %} record. Only use code systems appropriate for this record type (research-only systems like phecode, atc, and umls_cui are prohibited).

--- example output ---

